recommendations.long_description: 121 kilometres, 7554 m altitude differential: These hard facts of the Sdtirol Ultra Skyrace alone instil a great amount of respect in all extreme athletes. An absence of vertigo and surefootedness are absolute prerequisites to meet this challenge because on this tour you run in the high Alpine terrain of the Sarntal Alps.
recommendations.short_description: Every year at the end of July during the Sdtirol Ultra Skyrace event lots of extreme athletes run on this demanding trailrunning route in South Tyrol. But of course, you can face this challenge also in the rest of the year.
recommendations.title: South Tyrol Ultra Skyrace - Percorso ultra

recommendations.long_description: The hike from Vevani to Gorna Belica is a beautiful and scenic route that takes you through wild beech forests on the foothills of the Jablanica mountain range. Starting in the mountain town of Vevani, which is known for its traditional architecture and picturesque setting, the hike passes the famous Vevani springs and the Jankov Kamen Mountain Hut. The trail is well-marked for most parts and takes you to Gorna Belica, a small mountain village sitting at an altitude of over 1,400 meters above sea level and overlooking the plains north of Lake Ohrid. You can explore cultural landmarks such as the old church and the new mosque in the village and take in the scenery of the majestic Jablanica mountains. Overall, the hike from Vevcani to Gorna Belica is a challenging but rewarding experience that offers stunning views of the Macedonian countryside and a chance to immerse yourself in the local culture.
recommendations.short_description: A beautiful hike from the charming town of Vevani to the hidden mountain village of Gorna Belica on the slopes of majestic Jablanica in North Macedonia.
recommendations.title: From Vevani to the mystical mountain village of Gorna Belica
